How to run Maven Project through Command Prompt

Steps:

1. Open Command Prompt
2. Type 'cd' and then 'Enter' to Confirm Current Directory
3. Type 'cd C:\give project directory path and then Enter - Directory should change to the project directory
4. Type 'mvn complie' to comiple the maven project - If you see "Build Success" message at the end then it's fine
5. Type 'mvn test' to execute the tests on the command prompt - Check the message. "Build Failure" or "Build Success"

Maven test can also be 'run' from pom.xml file in Eclipse
